 <text id="B0704T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Waldo informs Mr. Keys that teachers will be available for a newly proposed school. Keys has
     a choice of which teacher to accept.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF &amp; AL</abbr> 4th <abbr
      expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9 <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub Dist</abbr>
     <name type="recipient">Harry Keys <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr><lb/>Waynesboro</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1868-11-23"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 23/68</date>
      <name type="place">Staunton</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>Sir:</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>In reply to your request for a teacher at Waynesboro I have the honor to inform you that Mr.
     Brackett <abbr expan="Superintendent">Supt</abbr> of schools for the Valley will furnish
     teacher on the following condition: that the freedpeople will board &amp; furnish fuel
     &amp; pay him (teacher) $10<hi rend="underline">
      <hi rend="super">00</hi>
     </hi> per month.</p>

    <p>Mr. Waring (colored) <unclear>representing</unclear> another association in the <orig
      reg="Valley">Vally</orig> will furnish teacher on same terms by paying $5<hi rend="underline">
      <hi rend="super">00</hi>
     </hi> per month - Please inform me immediately which proposition you accept if either. - I, of
     course, recommend the latter.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Very respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="obedient">obt</abbr> servant</salute>
     <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">ASA
     Comr</abbr></signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
